messages.message: Yeah we should def have this in the docs or even in the app itself

It mostly depends on what kind of model they were training in terms of specifics, but in broad strokes, they would need to:

1) Collect a dataset
2) Create an Annotator tool palette that provided information for the model they wanted to train
3) Annotate the docs
4) Provide us access to everything (both the docs and annotations)

There isn’t any explicit “export” step needed because for that to become relevant we’d need to be talking about a very specific model (e.g., train a model to detect mentions of this phhrase, etc etc)
